ALC Communications Corp said iturged the U.S. District Court in Washington not to allow theregional Bell companies to offer long distance telephoneservices.    ALC, parent of Allnet Communications Services, a longdistance carrier, said it made the request in comments filedwith the court on a Department of Justice proposal to free theregional Bell companies from various business restrictions.Under terms of the divestiture of American Telephone andTelegraph Co &lt;T>, the Bell companies are prohibited fromproviding long distance services. Reuter&#3;